# Design System & Style Guide

> Architectural blueprint on white marble — quiet efficiency, poppy where it counts.
>
> This file is the single source of truth for the visual language of this product.
> When generating UI, **always** consult this guide before writing styles. Match these
> tokens exactly. Do not invent new colors, font sizes, radii, or spacing values.

---

## 1. Design Philosophy

The product takes its visual cues from **Stripe**: a serene white canvas, structured
grid layouts, and a single vibrant violet that owns every call-to-action. The
personality is **modern and poppy** — large light-weight display type, expressive
radial gradients in hero moments, generous whitespace — but the day-to-day surface
is **calm, dense, and useable**: fine borders, compact rhythm, low-contrast neutrals,
and very few rounded corners.

Five rules that override everything else:

1. **One brand color does the work.** Deep Violet (`#533afd`) is the only color allowed
   on primary actions, focused inputs, active states, and key brand accents. Do not
   substitute blue, teal, or any other "primary."
2. **Light weights, large sizes.** Display and heading type use weight **300**, never
   600/700/800. Boldness comes from scale and color, not stroke thickness.
3. **Whitespace is a feature.** Use the 4 px spacing grid. Sections breathe at 64–96 px;
   cards stay tight at 12–24 px.
4. **Pop only in hero moments.** Multi-stop gradients (Sunburst, Dreamy, Fuchsia Glow)
   are reserved for hero sections, marketing surfaces, and decorative illustration —
   never as button or card backgrounds in the app shell.
5. **Sharp, not bubbly.** Border radius is **4 px** for everything interactive (buttons,
   inputs, tags) and **6 px** for cards. Never use `rounded-full`, `rounded-2xl`, or
   anything > 8 px on UI chrome.

---

## 2. Color Tokens

Use the CSS custom properties below. Tailwind classes map to the same tokens — see
section 12 for the full Tailwind v4 `@theme` block.

### 2.1 Brand

| Token                  | Hex       | Role                                                                          |
| ---------------------- | --------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `--color-deep-violet`  | `#533afd` | Primary CTAs, links, focus rings, active states, key brand icons              |
| `--color-soft-violet`  | `#8087ff` | Decorative icons, gradient highlights, hover glow                             |
| `--color-washed-violet`| `#b9b9f9` | Outlined-button border, subtle accent fills, selected-row backgrounds at 20%  |

### 2.2 Neutrals (text & surface)

| Token                   | Hex       | Role                                                          |
| ----------------------- | --------- | ------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `--color-midnight-ink`  | `#061b31` | Primary text, critical headings, icons on light surfaces      |
| `--color-slate-blue`    | `#50617a` | Secondary text, muted links, captions, descriptions           |
| `--color-ghost-gray`    | `#64748d` | Tertiary text, placeholders, disabled labels, inactive icons  |
| `--color-stone-gray`    | `#d8d6df` | Hairline rules, subtle borders, dividers                      |
| `--color-powder-blue`   | `#e5edf5` | Alternating section bg, default card surface, table zebras    |
| `--color-porcelain`     | `#f8fafd` | Slightly elevated surface, light input bg                     |
| `--color-platinum`      | `#ffffff` | Page background, primary card surface, button text on dark    |

### 2.3 Semantic accents (use sparingly — outlines & badges only)

| Token                    | Hex       | Role                                                       |
| ------------------------ | --------- | ---------------------------------------------------------- |
| `--color-accent-green`   | `#81b81a` | Success outlines, positive deltas, "live" status pip       |
| `--color-vibrant-orange` | `#ff6118` | Warning outlines, "new" / "beta" badges, alert dividers    |
| `--color-fuchsia`        | `#ff2ede` | Decorative gradient stop only — never as a flat fill       |

### 2.4 Decorative gradients (HERO ONLY)

```css
--gradient-sunburst: linear-gradient(
  90deg,
  rgb(114, 50, 241) 3.13%,
  rgb(251, 118, 250) 50%,
  rgb(255, 207, 94)
);

--gradient-dreamy: radial-gradient(
  circle,
  rgb(127, 125, 252),
  rgb(244, 75, 204) 33%,
  rgb(229, 237, 245) 66%
);

--gradient-fuchsia-glow: linear-gradient(
  0deg,
  rgb(255, 46, 222),
  rgb(210, 152, 255)
);

/* Stripe's signature animated mesh — 4 stops, slowly rotating in a WebGL canvas */
--gradient-mesh-stops: #6ec3f4, #3a3aff, #ff61ab, #E63946;
```

**Use cases:** marketing hero sections, empty-state illustrations, auth screens,
splash/loading panels, decorative side panels in onboarding. **Never** on buttons,
inputs, navbars, modal backgrounds, or text fills inside the app shell.

### 2.5 Color usage rules

- Default page background is `--color-platinum` (`#ffffff`). Alternate sections may
  use `--color-powder-blue` for visual rhythm.
- Body text is `--color-midnight-ink`. Secondary text drops to `--color-slate-blue`,
  never lighter than `--color-ghost-gray` for legibility.
- Links use `--color-deep-violet` with no underline by default; underline appears on
  hover (1 px, `currentColor`, 2 px offset).
- Focus ring is **always** a 2 px outline of `--color-deep-violet` at 40 % alpha,
  with a 2 px offset. Never remove focus rings.
- All color pairs must meet **WCAG AA** (4.5:1 for body, 3:1 for large text).
  `--color-ghost-gray` on white is borderline — only use it for ≥ 14 px non-essential
  text.

---

## 3. Typography

### 3.1 Font stack

The reference face is **Söhne** by Klim Type Foundry (variable, OpenType `ss01` + `tnum`).
Söhne is a paid licensed font; for this project the substitute is **Inter** (variable,
free via Google Fonts / `next/font`), which mirrors Söhne's proportions closely.

```css
--font-sans:
  "Inter", "Söhne", system-ui, -apple-system, "Segoe UI", Roboto,
  "Helvetica Neue", Arial, sans-serif;

--font-mono:
  "JetBrains Mono", "Source Code Pro", ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular,
  Menlo, Consolas, monospace;

/* enable stylistic alt + tabular numerals globally */
font-feature-settings: "ss01" on, "tnum" on, "cv11" on;
```

When loading Inter, request weights **300, 400, 500** only. Weight 600+ is forbidden
for product UI (allowed for code/badges if absolutely necessary).

### 3.2 Type scale (modular, base 16 px, ratio ≈ 1.2)

| Role            | Size   | Weight | Line-height | Letter-spacing | Token              |
| --------------- | ------ | ------ | ----------- | -------------- | ------------------ |
| Display Hero    | 56 px  | 300    | 1.03        | -0.030 em      | `--text-display`   |
| Display Large   | 48 px  | 300    | 1.07        | -0.025 em      | `--text-display-lg`|
| Heading XL      | 44 px  | 300    | 1.10        | -0.022 em      | `--text-heading-xl`|
| Heading L       | 32 px  | 300    | 1.10        | -0.020 em      | `--text-heading-l` |
| Heading M       | 26 px  | 400    | 1.12        | -0.012 em      | `--text-heading-m` |
| Heading S       | 22 px  | 400    | 1.20        | -0.010 em      | `--text-heading-s` |
| Subheading      | 18 px  | 400    | 1.40        | -0.009 em      | `--text-subheading`|
| Body Large      | 18 px  | 400    | 1.50        | normal         | `--text-body-lg`   |
| Body            | 16 px  | 400    | 1.50        | normal         | `--text-body`      |
| Body Small      | 14 px  | 400    | 1.45        | normal         | `--text-body-sm`   |
| Caption         | 12 px  | 400    | 1.45        | 0.01 em        | `--text-caption`   |
| Code            | 13 px  | 500    | 1.60        | normal         | `--text-code`      |
| Code Label      | 12 px  | 500    | 1.00        | 0.06 em + UPPER| `--text-code-label`|

### 3.3 Typography rules

- Display and `heading-xl/l` are **weight 300** — never bump to 500/600 for "emphasis."
  Use scale or color contrast instead.
- Headings hug their content: tight `line-height` (1.03–1.20) and **negative**
  letter-spacing.
- Body copy keeps a **comfortable** `line-height` of 1.4–1.5 and **zero or
  positive** letter-spacing. Never tighten body text.
- Long-form prose max width: **65–72 ch**. Never run body text the full width of a
  desktop viewport.
- Numbers in tables, dashboards, and any aligned columns must use `font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums`.
- Do not use `text-transform: uppercase` except for the `code-label` style (eyebrow
  labels above hero headings) and pill-style status badges.
- Headings use sentence case. Buttons use sentence case. Only eyebrow labels and
  status badges may use UPPERCASE.

---

## 4. Spacing & Layout

Base unit: **4 px**. Density: **comfortable**. The grid is non-negotiable.

```
--spacing-1:  4px
--spacing-2:  8px
--spacing-3: 12px
--spacing-4: 16px
--spacing-5: 20px
--spacing-6: 24px
--spacing-7: 28px
--spacing-8: 32px
--spacing-9: 36px
--spacing-10: 40px
--spacing-12: 48px
--spacing-15: 60px
--spacing-16: 64px
--spacing-20: 80px
--spacing-24: 96px
--spacing-32: 128px
```

### 4.1 Standard rhythm

- **Element gap** (related items in a row/stack): `8 px`
- **Group gap** (between input + label, label + help text): `8 px` / `4 px`
- **Card padding**: `24 px` desktop, `16 px` mobile (`12 px` only for compact info-dense cards)
- **Section vertical gap**: `64 px` desktop, `48 px` mobile
- **Hero vertical gap**: `96 px` to `128 px`
- **Page gutter**: `24 px` mobile, `32 px` tablet, `48 px+` desktop
- **Container max-width**: `1200 px` (content), `1440 px` (full bleed marketing)

### 4.2 Layout patterns

- Mobile-first. Use a 4 / 8 / 12-column responsive grid (4 mobile, 8 tablet, 12 desktop).
- Hero sections are full-bleed; everything else is centered in a max-width container.
- Alternate section backgrounds between `--color-platinum` and `--color-powder-blue`
  to create rhythm without rules.
- Sticky top nav is `64 px` tall on desktop, `56 px` on mobile, with a 1 px hairline
  bottom border in `--color-stone-gray`.

---

## 5. Border Radius

Stripe is **sharp**. Keep it that way.

| Element         | Radius |
| --------------- | ------ |
| Buttons         | `4 px` |
| Inputs / select | `4 px` |
| Tags / chips    | `4 px` (use `9999 px` only for status pips) |
| Images / avatars| `4 px` (avatars may be `9999 px`)           |
| Cards           | `6 px` |
| Modal / sheet   | `8 px` |
| Tooltips        | `4 px` |

Anything beyond `8 px` on a rectangular UI element is forbidden.

---

## 6. Elevation & Shadows

Shadows are **soft and diffused**, never sharp drop shadows.

```css
--shadow-sm:  rgba(23, 23, 23, 0.06)  0px 3px  6px 0px;
--shadow-md:  rgba(50, 50, 93, 0.08)  0px 8px  16px 0px;
--shadow-lg:  rgba(23, 23, 23, 0.08)  0px 15px 35px 0px;
--shadow-xl:  rgba(50, 50, 93, 0.12)  0px 16px 32px 0px;
--shadow-glow:rgba(83, 58, 253, 0.20) 0px 0px  32px 8px;  /* hero / hovered card */

--ring-focus: 0 0 0 2px rgba(83, 58, 253, 0.40);
```

### Elevation levels

| Level | Surface             | Shadow              |
| ----- | ------------------- | ------------------- |
| 0     | Page bg             | none                |
| 1     | Default card        | `--shadow-sm`       |
| 2     | Hovered card        | `--shadow-xl`       |
| 3     | Floating menu / popover | `--shadow-lg`   |
| 4     | Modal               | `--shadow-xl`       |
| 5     | Hero feature card   | `--shadow-glow`     |

Cards default to **no shadow + 1 px border** in `--color-stone-gray`. Add
`--shadow-sm` on hover. Reserve `--shadow-glow` for marketing hero cards only.

---

## 7. Components

### 7.1 Buttons

Height is fixed at **40 px** (default) or **48 px** (large / hero CTA).
Padding is symmetric around centered text + optional 16 px icon.

| Variant       | BG                  | Text                | Border                       | Notes                       |
| ------------- | ------------------- | ------------------- | ---------------------------- | --------------------------- |
| Primary       | `--color-deep-violet` | `#fff`            | none                         | Default for the main action |
| Secondary     | `--color-platinum`  | `--color-midnight-ink` | 1 px `--color-stone-gray` | Side-by-side with Primary   |
| Outlined      | transparent         | `--color-deep-violet` | 1 px `--color-washed-violet` | Tertiary CTA              |
| Ghost         | transparent         | `--color-midnight-ink` | none                       | Toolbar / inline action     |
| Destructive   | transparent         | `#c0392b`           | 1 px `#c0392b`               | Confirm-step only           |

- Radius `4 px`. Padding `0 24 px` (default) or `0 28 px` (large).
- Font: 16 px / weight 400 / line-height 1.0 / letter-spacing `-0.005em`.
- Hover on Primary: brightness `1.08` + 1 px translateY(-0.5 px) + `--shadow-md`.
- Active: brightness `0.96`, no translate.
- Disabled: 40 % opacity, no shadow, `cursor: not-allowed`.
- Loading: replace label with a 16 px spinner; preserve width to avoid layout shift.
- Full-width buttons only on mobile or in narrow forms (≤ 360 px).

### 7.2 Inputs (text, email, number, select, textarea)

- Height `40 px` (single-line), padding `0 12 px`.
- BG `--color-platinum`, border 1 px `--color-stone-gray`, radius `4 px`.
- Label: 14 px / weight 500 / `--color-midnight-ink`, sits 4 px above the input.
- Help text: 12 px / `--color-slate-blue`, 4 px below the input.
- Error: border + help text → `#c0392b`; do **not** turn the input background red.
- Focus: border → `--color-deep-violet`, plus `--ring-focus`.
- Placeholder: `--color-ghost-gray`, never italic.

### 7.3 Cards

```css
.card {
  background: var(--color-platinum);
  border: 1px solid var(--color-stone-gray);
  border-radius: 6px;
  padding: 24px;
  transition: box-shadow 200ms ease, transform 200ms ease;
}
.card:hover { box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm); }

.card--feature {        /* marketing / dashboard hero card */
  background: var(--color-porcelain);
  border: none;
  box-shadow: var(--shadow-glow);
}

.card--muted {          /* secondary surface */
  background: var(--color-powder-blue);
  border: none;
}
```

### 7.4 Navigation

- Top bar: `64 px` tall, sticky, white bg, 1 px hairline bottom border.
- Logo on the left (24 px height), nav links centered or left-aligned, account
  controls right.
- Nav link: 14 px / weight 400 / `--color-midnight-ink`, 8 px vertical padding.
  Hover sets text to `--color-deep-violet` only — no underline, no background.
- Active route gets a 2 px violet underline `1 px below baseline`.
- Sidebar (app shell): 240 px wide, `--color-porcelain` bg, items 36 px tall,
  4 px radius, 12 px padding. Selected item bg = `--color-washed-violet` at 30 %.

### 7.5 Tables

- 1 px hairline `--color-stone-gray` between rows. **No vertical** borders.
- Row height `48 px`. Cell padding `12 px 16 px`.
- Header: 12 px / weight 500 / UPPERCASE / `--color-slate-blue` /
  letter-spacing `0.04 em`.
- Numeric cells: tabular nums, right-aligned.
- Hover row: bg `--color-porcelain`.
- Zebra striping is **off** by default; turn on (`--color-porcelain` on odd rows)
  only for tables > 8 columns.

### 7.6 Tags / badges / status pips

- Tag: 4 px radius, 12 px font, weight 500, padding `4 px 8 px`.
- Status pip: 8 px circle, optionally with a 12 px label next to it.
- Map status to color outlines (not fills):
  - **Live / success** → `--color-accent-green`
  - **Pending / warning** → `--color-vibrant-orange`
  - **Failed / error** → `#c0392b`
  - **Info / neutral** → `--color-slate-blue`

### 7.7 Modals & sheets

- Modal: max-width `560 px`, 8 px radius, 32 px padding, `--shadow-xl`,
  centered overlay with `rgba(6, 27, 49, 0.40)` scrim.
- Sheet (mobile): full width, anchored bottom, 12 px top radius, 24 px padding.
- Always trap focus, return focus on close, support `Esc` to dismiss.

### 7.8 Toasts

- Bottom-right, 360 px max width, 8 px radius, white bg, 1 px border, `--shadow-lg`.
- Auto-dismiss `5000 ms`, with a thin progress hairline in `--color-deep-violet`.

---

## 8. Iconography

- Use **Lucide** (or Phosphor) outline icons at **1.5 px** stroke.
- Default size `16 px` inline, `20 px` in buttons, `24 px` in nav.
- Color inherits `currentColor`. Never apply gradients to functional icons.
- Decorative icons in marketing surfaces may use `--color-soft-violet` fills or
  the dreamy gradient, masked.

---

## 9. Motion & Interaction

- Default transition: `200 ms cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1)` (Material standard
  ease — Stripe-equivalent feel).
- Hover state changes: `150 ms`. Page transitions: `300 ms`. Modal in/out: `220 ms`.
- Use `transform` and `opacity` only for animations — never animate `width`, `height`,
  `top`, or `left`.
- Hero gradient meshes animate slowly: full rotation cycle ≥ `12 s`, never distracting.
- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion`: disable parallax, skew, gradient animation, and
  anything looped.

---

## 10. Accessibility (non-negotiable)

- WCAG **2.2 AA** minimum across the product.
- Contrast ratios validated: 4.5:1 for body text, 3:1 for ≥ 18 px or bold ≥ 14 px,
  3:1 for UI components and graphical objects.
- Every interactive control reachable by keyboard. Visible 2 px violet focus ring
  always present (use `:focus-visible`).
- All form fields have programmatically associated labels (`<label for>` or `aria-labelledby`).
- All icons that convey meaning have `aria-label`; purely decorative icons get
  `aria-hidden="true"`.
- Color is never the sole carrier of meaning — pair status colors with an icon or
  text label.
- Hit targets ≥ `44 × 44 px` on touch.
- Honor `prefers-reduced-motion` and `prefers-color-scheme` (dark mode roadmapped —
  see section 11).

---

## 11. Dark mode (roadmap)

When dark mode lands, surfaces invert as follows. Do **not** ship dark mode piecemeal:

| Light                    | → Dark                                  |
| ------------------------ | --------------------------------------- |
| `--color-platinum`       | `#0a0e1a`                               |
| `--color-porcelain`      | `#111726`                               |
| `--color-powder-blue`    | `#1a2235`                               |
| `--color-stone-gray`     | `#2a3245`                               |
| `--color-midnight-ink`   | `#f8fafd`                               |
| `--color-slate-blue`     | `#9aa7be`                               |
| `--color-deep-violet`    | `#7c66ff` (raise lightness ~ 8 %)       |

Until then, build everything in light mode and avoid hardcoded `#fff` / `#000`
in component code — always reference tokens.

---

## 12. Implementation

### 12.1 CSS variables (drop-in `:root` block)

```css
:root {
  /* Brand */
  --color-deep-violet: #533afd;
  --color-soft-violet: #8087ff;
  --color-washed-violet: #b9b9f9;

  /* Neutrals */
  --color-midnight-ink: #061b31;
  --color-slate-blue: #50617a;
  --color-ghost-gray: #64748d;
  --color-stone-gray: #d8d6df;
  --color-powder-blue: #e5edf5;
  --color-porcelain: #f8fafd;
  --color-platinum: #ffffff;

  /* Accents */
  --color-accent-green: #81b81a;
  --color-vibrant-orange: #ff6118;
  --color-fuchsia: #ff2ede;
  --color-danger: #c0392b;

  /* Gradients */
  --gradient-sunburst: linear-gradient(90deg, #7232f1 3.13%, #fb76fa 50%, #ffcf5e);
  --gradient-dreamy: radial-gradient(circle, #7f7dfc, #f44bcc 33%, #e5edf5 66%);
  --gradient-fuchsia-glow: linear-gradient(0deg, #ff2ede, #d298ff);

  /* Spacing (4px grid) */
  --space-1: 4px;   --space-2: 8px;   --space-3: 12px;  --space-4: 16px;
  --space-5: 20px;  --space-6: 24px;  --space-8: 32px;  --space-10: 40px;
  --space-12: 48px; --space-16: 64px; --space-20: 80px; --space-24: 96px;

  /* Radius */
  --radius-sm: 4px;
  --radius-md: 6px;
  --radius-lg: 8px;
  --radius-pill: 9999px;

  /* Shadows */
  --shadow-sm:  rgba(23, 23, 23, 0.06)  0px 3px  6px 0px;
  --shadow-md:  rgba(50, 50, 93, 0.08)  0px 8px  16px 0px;
  --shadow-lg:  rgba(23, 23, 23, 0.08)  0px 15px 35px 0px;
  --shadow-xl:  rgba(50, 50, 93, 0.12)  0px 16px 32px 0px;
  --shadow-glow: rgba(83, 58, 253, 0.20) 0px 0px  32px 8px;
  --ring-focus: 0 0 0 2px rgba(83, 58, 253, 0.40);

  /* Type */
  --font-sans: "Inter", "Söhne", system-ui, -apple-system, "Segoe UI", Roboto, "Helvetica Neue", Arial, sans-serif;
  --font-mono: "JetBrains Mono", "Source Code Pro", ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Consolas, monospace;

  /* Motion */
  --ease-out: cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1);
  --duration-fast: 150ms;
  --duration-base: 200ms;
  --duration-slow: 300ms;
}

html, body {
  background: var(--color-platinum);
  color: var(--color-midnight-ink);
  font-family: var(--font-sans);
  font-feature-settings: "ss01" on, "tnum" on, "cv11" on;
  -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
  text-rendering: optimizeLegibility;
}
```

### 12.2 Tailwind v4 `@theme`

```css
@import "tailwindcss";

@theme {
  --color-violet:        #533afd;
  --color-violet-soft:   #8087ff;
  --color-violet-washed: #b9b9f9;
  --color-ink:           #061b31;
  --color-slate:         #50617a;
  --color-ghost:         #64748d;
  --color-stone:         #d8d6df;
  --color-powder:        #e5edf5;
  --color-porcelain:     #f8fafd;
  --color-platinum:      #ffffff;
  --color-success:       #81b81a;
  --color-warning:       #ff6118;
  --color-danger:        #c0392b;

  --font-sans: "Inter", "Söhne", system-ui, sans-serif;
  --font-mono: "JetBrains Mono", ui-monospace, monospace;

  --radius-sm: 4px;
  --radius-md: 6px;
  --radius-lg: 8px;

  --shadow-soft:  0 3px  6px 0 rgb(23 23 23 / 0.06);
  --shadow-pop:   0 16px 32px 0 rgb(50 50 93 / 0.12);
  --shadow-glow:  0 0   32px 8px rgb(83 58 253 / 0.20);
}
```

### 12.3 Recommended stack (when adding code)

- **Framework:** Next.js (App Router) + React 19 + TypeScript (strict).
- **Styling:** Tailwind CSS v4 + CSS variables above. No CSS-in-JS runtimes.
- **Components:** shadcn/ui as the foundation, restyled to these tokens (replace
  default `--primary` with `--color-violet`, `--radius` with `4 px`).
- **Icons:** `lucide-react`.
- **Fonts:** `next/font/google` for Inter (weights 300, 400, 500), display=`swap`.
- **Animation:** Framer Motion for choreographed sequences only; CSS transitions
  for everything else.

---

## 13. AI authoring rules

When writing or modifying UI code in this repo, follow these instructions:

1. **Always import tokens, never hardcode.** Use `var(--color-deep-violet)` /
   `text-violet` / `bg-platinum`, never `#533afd` or `bg-[#533afd]` literals.
2. **Reuse component primitives** before building a new one. Check `components/ui/`
   first.
3. **Pick the smallest valid primitive.** A status pip is a `<span>`, not a `Card`.
4. **Match the type scale exactly.** If a heading "feels" like it should be 20 px,
   pick 18 px or 22 px from the scale — do not introduce 20 px.
5. **Spacing must come from the 4 px scale.** No `padding: 13px` or `gap: 7px`.
6. **No new fonts, ever.** If the design seems to call for one, use weight + size
   instead.
7. **Gradients are opt-in.** Default to flat surfaces. Only add a gradient when the
   user explicitly asks for "hero", "marketing", "splash", or "decorative."
8. **Ship accessible by default.** Every button has an accessible name, every input
   has a label, every focus state is visible, every interactive element is keyboard-
   reachable.
9. **Animate sparingly.** If you can't justify the motion in one sentence, remove it.
10. **Generate dark-mode-safe code.** Never write `bg-white` / `text-black` directly;
    always reference a token, even if dark mode is not yet active.

---

## 14. Quick reference cheatsheet

```
PRIMARY ACTION     bg-violet  text-platinum  rounded-[4px]  h-10  px-6   shadow-md(hover)
SECONDARY ACTION   bg-platinum text-ink  border-stone  rounded-[4px]  h-10  px-6
LINK               text-violet  hover:underline  underline-offset-2
HEADING (hero)     56px / 300 / -0.03em / ink
HEADING (section)  32px / 300 / -0.02em / ink
BODY               16px / 400 / 1.5    / ink
CAPTION            12px / 400 / 1.45   / slate
CARD               bg-platinum border-stone rounded-[6px] p-6 hover:shadow-sm
INPUT              h-10 px-3 rounded-[4px] border-stone focus:border-violet focus:ring-violet/40
SECTION GAP        py-16 (64px)  /  py-24 (96px hero)
PAGE GUTTER        px-6 md:px-8 lg:px-12
```

When in doubt: **white background, midnight text, one violet button, lots of
whitespace, light-weight headings.** That's the look.
